'''Benjamin August Gimmerthal''' (1779, [[Zittau]]- 1848, [[Riga]] (then [[Russian Empire]])) was a [[Germany|German]] [[entomologist]] who specialised in [[Diptera]]. His collection of [[Chloropidae]] is held by the Museum of Systematic Zoology, [[University of Latvia]], Riga. The remaining Diptera and other insects by the Natural History Museum of Latvia ([http://www.dabasmuzejs.gov.lv/en/frontpage Homepage])
