{{Infobox journal | title = Social Studies of Science | cover = Social Studies of Science.jpg | editor = Sergio Sismondo | discipline = [[Science and technology studies]], [[history of science]], [[philosophy of science]], [[sociology of science]] | former_names =Science Studies (until 1975, {{ISSN|0036-8539}}) | abbreviation = Soc. Stud. Sci. | publisher = [[SAGE Publications]] | country = | frequency = Bimonthly | history = 1971–present | openaccess = | license = | impact = 2.351 | impact-year = 2014 | website = http://www.sagepub.com/journalsProdDesc.nav?prodId=Journal200907 | link1 = http://sss.sagepub.com/content/current | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://sss.sagepub.com/content/by/year | link2-name = Online archive | JSTOR = | OCLC = 2242476 | LCCN = 75645506 | CODEN = | ISSN = 0306-3127 | eISSN = 1460-3659 }} '''''Social Studies of Science''''' is a bimonthly [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] that publishes papers relating to the [[History of science|history]] and [[philosophy of science]]. The journal's [[editor-in-chief]] is Sergio Sismondo ([[Queen's University]]). The journal was established in 1971 under the name ''Science Studies'' and assumed its present title in 1975. It is currently published by [[SAGE Publications]].
In the inaugural issue, the editors announced that the journal "will devote itself to original research, whether empirical or theoretical, which brings fresh light to bear on the concepts, processes and consequences of modern science. It will be interdisciplinary in the sense that it will encourage appropriate contributions from political science, sociology, economics, history, philosophy, social anthropology, and the legal and educational disciplines. It will welcome studies of fundamental research, applied research and development; of university science, industrial science and science in government."<ref>{{cite journal|author=The Editors|title=Editorial|journal=Science Studies|date=January 1971|volume=1|issue=1|pages=2}}</ref>
== Abstracting and indexing == ''Social Studies of Science'' is abstracted and indexed in [[Scopus]] and the [[Social Sciences Citation Index]]. According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', its 2014 [[impact factor]] is 2.351, ranking it 1st out of 59 journals in the category "History of Philosophy and Science".<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2015 |chapter=Journals Ranked by Impact: History of Philosophy and Science|title=2014 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Social Sciences |accessdate=2011-09-30 |work=Web of Science |postscript=.}}</ref>
